Understood. I have corrected the notes to combine the configuration steps and removed the specific "activate" instruction as requested.

Here are the revised short notes:

Migration Checklist: OmniStudio Standard Runtime
I. Setup & Configuration
Disable Managed Package Runtime:

Navigate to Setup → OmniStudio Settings and disable "Managed Package Runtime".

Ensure Runtime Compatibility:

Open OmniScripts & FlexCards and ensure "Deploy standardruntime compatibility" is checked, OR

Enable the global setting: "Deploy Custom Lightning Web Components in Standard Runtime" (in Setup).

Disable Designer:

Disable "Managed Package Designer".

II. LWC Code Updates (Wrapper Implementation)
Replace existing OmniScript tags with the Standard Runtime Wrapper in parent LWCs.

Old Tag:

HTML
<c-business-detail-english prefill={prefillData} layout="lightning"></c-business-detail-english>
New Wrapper Tag:

HTML
<omnistudio-omnistudio-standard-runtime-wrapper
    type="BusinessDetail"
    subtype="BusinessDetails"
    language="English"
    prefill={prefillData}>
</omnistudio-omnistudio-standard-runtime-wrapper>
III. Impacted Components
The following components require the wrapper update:

obr_OnboardingOmniStudio.html

obr_OfficialDetails

obr_OmniStudioMccWF

mccTabUtilityComponent

obr_CHSDetails

obr_IDandVDetails

obrMCC_ConnectedBusinessOSCall

onboardingMCCWFIDandV

onboardingMCCWFOfficialDetails

